229, Coss. L. Postumius Albinus ΙΙ., (see B. xxii. 35, and xxiii. 24‚) Cn. Fulvius Centumalus. First Illyrian war. Illyrians subdued, (see B. xxi. 16, note). (Death of Hamilcar in Spain; see note, B. xxi. ch. 2). Hasdrubal succeeds him in the command.

227, Coss. P. Valerius Flaccus, M. Atilius Regulus. Number of praetors increased from two to four.

226, Coss. M. Valerius Messala, L. Apustius Fullo.

22⁵. Coss. L. AEmilius Papus, C. Atilius Regulus. Sardinian insurrection—quelled by Atilius. Combination of Transalpine and Cisalpine Gauls: they are defeated by the Consul AEmilius. Atilius slain in the battle. Q. Fabius Pictor, the historian, who was cotemporary with L. Cincius Alimentus, (see note, B. xxi. 38,) served in this war.
